Mr Ri referred to a joint statement issued by Mr Kim Jong Un and Mr Donald Trump at the first summit between a incumbent US President and a North Korean leader in Singapore on June 12, where Mr Kim promised to work towards the "disposal of nuclear weapons on the Korean Peninsula" while Mr Trump promised guarantees for the security of North Korea.
North Korea has sought a formal end to the Korean war in 1950-53, but the United States has said that Pyongyang must first phase out its nuclear weapons.
